A3: SPL Library Checkouts

Introduction

An introduction of the data and a description of the trends/books/items you are choosing to analyze (and why!)

The data is recording different reading materials with different usage type like physical or digital. The trend I would like to analyze is the checkouts trend of digital, specifically Ebooks, to see in a modern days the portion of how many people choose to read electronic version materials.

Summary Information

Write a summary paragraph of findings that includes the 5 values calculated from your summary information R script

These will likely be calculated using your DPLYR skills, answering questions such as:

  • What is the average number of checkouts for each item?
  • What is the month or year with the most/least checkouts for a book that you’re interested in?
  • What is the month or year with the most/least checkouts for ebooks?
  • How has the number of print book checkouts changed over time?

Feel free to calculate and report values that you find relevant.

From the calculation I did, I find that “So You Want to Talk about Race (Unabridged)” is the digital book with the most monthly checkout amount(4903), and the book “Headphones / Seattle Public Library.” is the physical book with the most monthly checkout amount(2115). Also, in 2017, the book with the most monthly checkout amount(988) is “In Building Device Checkout”. Besides that, my favorite album 24K Magic has a highest checkout number at the year 2017. Last but not least, I find a increase trend of digital material checkout numbers over the checkout year, but in the year 2023, the number has a sudden decrease which might due to the data include checkouts only for the first two month of the year.

The Dataset

  • Who collected/published the data?
  • What are the parameters of the data (dates, number of checkouts, kinds of books, etc.)?
  • How was the data collected or generated?
  • Why was the data collected?
  • What, if any, ethical questions do you need to consider when working with this data?
  • What are possible limitations or problems with this data? (at least 200 words)

The data was collected by Seattle Public Library, the parameters in this dataset include Usage Class, Checkout Type, Material Type, Checkout Year, Checkout Month, Checkouts, Title, ISBN, Creator, Subjects, Publisher, Publication Year. The digital checkout data is from various media vendors, the physical data is from The Legrady artwork data archives. The data was collected for checking the trends of checkouts of different book in different sources like physical and digital. The ethical question that might be facing is what the book’s audiences is. When dealing with this, we need to be patient and reflecting the result using words that do not hurt their feelings.

The possible limitations with this data is there are many missing values that might be important when finding the trends that we needed. The missing value might form a false trend when we analyzing the data. Also the format of some variables are not the same, this cause a problem when we try to analyze the data that include the associated “untidy” data. We might need some time find a best way to clean up the data set before we start finding data visualization. Last but not least, we need to focus the category of the book, the physical and digital have different patterns and we need to be aware of what the observations belong to.
